reviewText: I REALLY ENJOYED THIS MOVIE VERY MUCH. I AM INTO HISTORICAL AND TRUE LAW CASES A LOT. ROB LOW IS A GREAT ACTOR.
Title: Prosecuting Casey Anthony

reviewText: I gave it four stares because some of the events that happened were not in the right order that it played out in real life.  Although, I love the real clips they used from the actual case.  Overall, I will watch this again.
Title: Prosecuting Casey Anthony

reviewText: I watched the footage of this poor child being lost,  and  I knew from the get go her mom was lying.  I am glad that they glamourize the "mother".  The movie was well-put together.  I am glad they kept actual Nancy grace footage.  Very sad for Caylee.  Her story needed to told.
Title: Prosecuting Casey Anthony

reviewText: Don't really know what I was thinking buying this and not renting it. It was okay your typical Lifetime movie. Not one of the better ones either.
Title: Prosecuting Casey Anthony

reviewText: This movie was done like an outline but without anything of value under the outline heading.  Rob Lowe, flat, boring and unconvincing as an actor.  I refuse to believe that this trial was as depicted in this movie.  Tiny snippets of information were mentioned with nothing to back them up.  No explanation of this "fictional?" nanny, was she real?  It made no sense and I guess I am glad I rented it if only to serve as a springboard for what not to watch.  Wow, amazingly bad.  I gave it two stars but I am taking one back.
Title: Prosecuting Casey Anthony
